See the comment in the AbstractViewAttachments action. 

I'd recommend cleaning up the distinction between the three different "we're uploading a file" objects, and making the fact the attachment might be an image a property of the helper object, not a subclass specialisation of it.

Eg the following is valid wiki markup:
{noformat}
[{cheese}|Home]
{noformat}

Unfortunately it:
* doesn't render as a link in the RTE
* doesn't round-trip back to the right wiki markup.  It converts back to

{noformat}
\[{cheese}\|Home\]
{noformat}

It was also broken in 2.10.0 but it did render as a link.  It just didn't round-trip correctly.  It round-tripped to:
{noformat}
[|Home]{cheese}
{noformat}

There are examples of this linking style in the Confluence demo space using the excerpt-include macro on the Example Sales Team page.

Add a new page, and enter markup:

{noformat}{gliffy:name=xxx}{noformat}

Switch to the Preview tab, and then click on the diagram placeholder.

System Error is returned:

{noformat}java.lang.ClassCastException: com.atlassian.confluence.pages.Draft
    at com.atlassian.confluence.pages.persistence.dao.hibernate.HibernateAbstractPageDao.getAbstractPageById(HibernateAbstractPageDao.java:17) {noformat}

Add an image to a page - this will generate wiki markup such as:
{noformat}!image.jpg!{noformat}

In the RTE, use the 'Edit Image' dialog, and click OK without making any changes.

Switch back to wiki markup - you now have:
{noformat}!image.jpg|width=320,height=240!{noformat}

