The {{\{recently-updated\}}} macro documentation states that you can include multiple spaces and negate spaces from selection:
From http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Recently+Updated+Macro#RecentlyUpdatedMacro-OptionalParameters:
{quote}
You can specify one or more space keys, separated by a comma or a space. 
To exclude content in a specific space, put a minus sign (-) immediately in front of that space key. For example: If you specify a space key of -BADSPACE you will get only content which is not in the BADSPACE.
{quote}
However, with the following markup:
{noformat}
h5.This should show nothing 
{recently-updated:spaces=-@all} 

h5.This should show everything except my own personal space 
{recently-updated:spaces=@all,-~pdzwart}
{noformat}
You do not end up with what you expect:
!http://img.skitch.com/20090519-dnird57d3geih6s4m4gqben8uj.jpg!

Proof of concept: https://qa-cac.atlassian.com/display/~pdzwart/Recently+updated+space+negation

Using a macro as the title of a tasklist macro, causes the tasklist to not render, but the macro used as the title does:
{noformat:title=Wiki markup}
{tasklist:{cheese}}
{noformat}

!http://img.skitch.com/20090519-p69pf4gte5xt6gyd9hxcgc4456.jpg!

Proof of concept: https://qa-cac.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=180292110

Use markup:
{noformat}[alias|Home]{noformat}

With the RTE on IE, highlight the link, and use the Macro Browser to enclose it in a column macro.

Now switch back to wiki markup - the link has been corrupted:
{noformat}[|Home]{column}[alias|Home][|Home]{column}{noformat}

Use markup:
{noformat}[aliastext|TEST:Page]{noformat}

Log in as a user with no permission to view space TEST, and edit the page.

Roundtripping from markup to RTE will then corrupt the link to:

{noformat}[aliastext]{noformat}

{noformat}
[S:\directory1\--budget--\directory3\2009.xls|_link_to_somewhere]
[S:\directory5\~dhergert\directory8\myfile.doc|_link_to_anotherplace]
{noformat}
The above markup displays the following incorrect link text:

S:\directory1-budget-\directory3\2009.xls
S:\directory5~dhergert\directory8\myfile.doc

It should display:
{noformat}
S:\directory1\--budget--\directory3\2009.xls
S:\directory5\~dhergert\directory8\myfile.doc
{noformat}

